# Key Documentation Principles

- Clear > Fancy
- Structured > Paragraph-heavy
- Practical > Theoretical
- Reproducible steps only
- No unnecessary storytelling
- Use code blocks properly
- Keep sections logically ordered

---

# When Creating a New Repository

Follow this order:

1. Title
2. Short description
3. Overview
4. Requirements
5. Features
6. Installation
7. Configuration
8. Usage
9. API / Topics
10. Structure
11. Troubleshooting
12. Author
13. License

If this structure is followed, the repository will meet professional engineering documentation standards.
